cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GT, cs.RO

This paper is focused on evaluating the performance of different exploration algorithms within the context of reinforcement learning. As such, it is likely to fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses the Arcade Learning Environment (ALE) to test the algorithms, which involves analyzing visual input from games, suggesting that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of different exploration methods on game performance, which could be seen as a game theory (cs.GT) problem. Finally, the use of reinforcement learning algorithms to control agents in a simulated environment could be seen as a robotics (cs.RO) problem.
